      "content": "It's completely understandable to feel this way given what you're experiencing, and it takes a lot of courage to acknowledge these struggles. However, it's important to remember that everyone is unique, and healing is a very personal journey. It's not easy to find the right fit for therapy or support groups, but sometimes trying is one of the best steps you can take. Your feelings indicate deep pain, and offering to hear them freely can be the first step in finding a new path to healing, possibly revealing parts of you that hadn't been seen as salvageable. Reaching out or attempting to connect with a professional can hopefully bring forth the support you need to discover a new foundation of strength, even if it doesn't seem that way right now. You've always had more \"left to heal\" than you realize, and with the right support, you may find a way to piece together what feels like lost pieces of yourself.",
